TY  - JOUR
T1  - A reexamination of analysts' earnings forecasts for takeover targets
AU  - Brous, Peter A.
AU  - Kini, Omesh
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 33
IS  - 2
SP  - 201
EP  - 225
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/04/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(93)90004-U
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X9390004U
AB  - We examine analysts' earnings forecasts for a sample of takeover targets and document that the announcement-month forecasts are systematically revised upward, supporting the hypothesis that a takeover announcement conveys favorable information about the target firm. In addition, we find that abnormal forecast revisions of future stand-alone earnings are significantly greater for targets with low Tobin's q-ratios relative to targets with high q-ratios, lending further support to the information hypothesis. Finally, we provide evidence that managerial resistance to the takeover does not destroy value. Our results are in direct contrast to Pound (1988).
